This is almost the actual text of Daniel iii. 51. The respond for the Nativity in the Mozarabio Missal is arranged as follows :—

According to St. Germain, this respond was sung by boys (parvuli). Gregory of Tours assigns the singing of it to a deacon. The use at Tours2 may possibly have differed from that of Paris on this point. The Roman use in this respect underwent an important change at

the end of the sixth century.³
